From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mitchell Cohen <mitchell@agilebits.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:39:37 -0400
Subject: win: Adjust client size constraints for frame insets before clamping

Size constraints are given in client area coordinates when
WidgetSizeIsClientSize() is true. They need to be inflated by frame
insets before clamping the size of the HWND, otherwise the window
will be constrained to a smaller size than intended.

The inset correction in this CL was already present in OnGetMinMaxInfo
which allows windows to be created with accurate size constraints.
I added it to AdjustedContentBounds and SizeWindowToAspectRatio so they
handle constraints the same way when bounds change.

The issue was discovered in Electron and is less obvious in Chrome
because browser windows don't currently set max size constraints, but
treating coordinates consistently benefits Chrome and all consumers.

Bug: 506480944
Change-Id: I237ee9f791fe01eeee295dec7bd2a88cae305652

diff --git a/ui/views/widget/desktop_aura/desktop_window_tree_host_win.cc b/ui/views/widget/desktop_aura/desktop_window_tree_host_win.cc
